description._content: TITLE Central Square in Keene NH CREATOR Whitehouse SUBJECT Buildings - NH - Keene Town squares DESCRIPTION Photograph of the Central Square in Keene New Hampshire. "This photograph, made near the middle of the winter of 1906-07, is remarkable for the absence of snow. It contains a number of former landmarks, such as the band stand, built in 1904 and removed in 1913, and the "wigwam" covering the fountain, erected to the memory of Allan Parkhurst Ingersoll. The fountain was damaged on the night of July 3rd, 1898, by a cannon cracker. It was repaired but in a few years was removed and its present whereabouts are unknown." PUBLISHER Keene Public Library DATE DIGITAL 20080204 DATE ORIGINAL 1906 RESOURCE TYPE photographic postcards FORMAT image/jpg RESOURCE IDENTIFIER hsykcsq046 RIGHTS MANAGMENT No known restriction on publication.
